---
layout: base.njk
title: Home
---

<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1 class="hero-title">🎮 Hunt Down the Best RAM Deals</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Compare RAM prices across retailers. Find the best deals on DDR5, DDR4, DDR3, SODIMM laptop memory, and ECC server RAM with price-per-GB calculations.</p>
      <div class="hero-stats">
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-value">{{ products.products | length }}</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Products</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-value">{{ categories | length }}</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Categories</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-value">7</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Retailers</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="products" class="products-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="affiliate-disclosure">
      💡 Affiliate Disclosure: This site earns commissions from qualifying purchases through affiliate links at no extra cost to you. <a href="/privacy/">Learn more</a>.
    </div>
    
    <div class="controls">
      <div class="filter-group">
        <label for="category-filter" class="filter-label">Category</label>
        <select id="category-filter" class="filter-select">
          <option value="">All Categories</option>
          <option value="DDR5">DDR5</option>
          <option value="DDR4">DDR4</option>
          <option value="DDR3">DDR3</option>
          <option value="SODIMM">SODIMM (Laptop)</option>
          <option value="ECC">ECC (Server)</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      
      <div class="filter-group">
        <label for="retailer-filter" class="filter-label">Retailer</label>
        <select id="retailer-filter" class="filter-select">
          <option value="">All Retailers</option>
          <option value="Amazon">Amazon</option>
          <option value="Newegg">Newegg</option>
          <option value="Best Buy">Best Buy</option>
          <option value="B&H">B&H Photo</option>
          <option value="Corsair">Corsair</option>
          <option value="G.Skill">G.Skill</option>
          <option value="Kingston">Kingston</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      
      <div class="filter-group">
        <label for="condition-filter" class="filter-label">Condition</label>
        <select id="condition-filter" class="filter-select">
          <option value="">All Conditions</option>
          <option value="New">New</option>
          <option value="Used">Used</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      
      <div class="filter-group">
        <label for="sort-filter" class="filter-label">Sort By</label>
        <select id="sort-filter" class="filter-select">
          <option value="pricePerGB-asc">Price/GB (Low to High)</option>
          <option value="pricePerGB-desc">Price/GB (High to Low)</option>
          <option value="price-asc">Total Price (Low to High)</option>
          <option value="price-desc">Total Price (High to Low)</option>
          <option value="capacity-desc">Capacity (High to Low)</option>
          <option value="capacity-asc">Capacity (Low to High)</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      
      <div class="search-group">
        <label for="search-input" class="filter-label">Search</label>
        <input type="text" id="search-input" class="search-input" placeholder="Search products...">
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="results-info">
      <span id="results-count">{{ products.products | length }} products found</span>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Product Cards Grid -->
    <div class="products-grid" id="products-grid">
      {% for product in products.products %}
      <article class="product-card" 
               data-category="{{ product.category }}" 
               data-retailer="{{ product.retailer }}" 
               data-condition="{{ product.condition }}"
               data-name="{{ product.name | lower }}"
               data-price-per-gb="{{ product.pricePerGB }}"
               data-price="{{ product.price }}"
               data-capacity-gb="{{ product.capacity }}">
        
        <!-- Badges -->
        <div class="card-header">
          <div class="card-badges">
            <span class="badge badge-{{ product.category | slug }}">{{ product.category }}</span>
            <span class="condition-badge condition-{{ product.condition | slug }}">{{ product.condition }}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Product Name -->
        <h3 class="product-name">{{ product.name }}</h3>
        <p class="product-subcategory">{{ product.subcategory }}</p>
        
        <!-- Price Per GB - THE VISUAL HERO -->
        <div class="price-hero">
          <span class="price-hero-label">Price per GB</span>
          <span class="price-per-gb">${{ product.pricePerGB | formatNumber }}</span>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Details -->
        <div class="card-details">
          <div class="detail-row">
            <span class="detail-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="6" width="20" height="12" rx="2"/><path d="M12 12h.01"/><path d="M17 12h.01"/><path d="M7 12h.01"/></svg>
              Capacity
            </span>
            <span class="detail-value capacity-value">
              <span class="capacity-number">{{ product.capacity }}</span>
              <span class="capacity-unit">GB</span>
            </span>
          </div>
          
          <div class="detail-row">
            <span class="detail-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M16 8h-6a2 2 0 1 0 0 4h4a2 2 0 1 1 0 4H8"/><path d="M12 18V6"/></svg>
              Total Price
            </span>
            <span class="detail-value price-value">${{ product.price | formatNumber }}</span>
          </div>
          
          <div class="detail-row">
            <span class="detail-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 2L3 6v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V6l-3-4z"/><line x1="3" y1="6" x2="21" y2="6"/><path d="M16 10a4 4 0 0 1-8 0"/></svg>
              Retailer
            </span>
            <span class="detail-value retailer-badge">{{ product.retailer }}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Buy Button -->
        <div class="card-footer">
          <a href="{{ product.url }}" 
             target="_blank" 
             rel="noopener"
             class="buy-link">
            View Deal
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="7" y1="17" x2="17" y2="7"/><polyline points="7 7 17 7 17 17"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    
    <!-- No Results -->
    <div id="no-results" class="no-results" style="display: none;">
      <div class="no-results-icon">🔍</div>
      <h3>No products found</h3>
      <p>Try adjusting your filters or search terms to find what you're looking for.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="about" class="about-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">About RamHunter.com</h2>
    <div class="about-content">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>RamHunter.com helps you find the best memory deals by calculating the true cost-per-gigabyte across different RAM types and retailers. Our mission is to help you make informed decisions when upgrading your system's memory, whether you're building a gaming PC, upgrading a laptop, or configuring a server.</p>
        <h3>Why Price Per GB?</h3>
        <p>When comparing memory, the total price can be misleading. A 64GB kit at $199 costs $3.11/GB, while a 32GB kit at $109 costs $3.41/GB — you're getting better value with the larger kit! The price-per-gigabyte metric gives you a fair comparison across different capacities.</p>
        <h3>Data Sources</h3>
        <p>Prices are fetched automatically from affiliate APIs and updated daily. All links include affiliate tags which help support this site at no extra cost to you. We earn a small commission on qualifying purchases.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-categories">
        <h3>Categories</h3>
        <ul class="category-list">
          <li><span class="category-icon">🚀</span><strong>DDR5</strong> — Latest Gen Desktop</li>
          <li><span class="category-icon">⚡</span><strong>DDR4</strong> — Current Gen Desktop</li>
          <li><span class="category-icon">📀</span><strong>DDR3</strong> — Legacy Systems</li>
          <li><span class="category-icon">💻</span><strong>SODIMM</strong> — Laptop Memory</li>
          <li><span class="category-icon">🖥️</span><strong>ECC</strong> — Server/Workstation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script src="{{ '/js/main.js' | url }}"></script>